Subject: [PATCH] F3: load show from LittleFS + host-tested applyLoadedShow

- apply_loaded_show.{h,cpp}: pure patch routing. Decides Raw vs Fixture per
  universe (matrix universes are Raw), routes sinks via ISinkFactory, patches
  every fixture + head geometry. Zero device deps.
- test_apply_loaded_show.cpp: 6 tests (routing, heads, matrix Raw, multi-univ
  matrix, unsupported transport, OOB fixture). ASAN-clean (fixed a dangling
  pointer in the test's factory: vector realloc -> fixed array).
- storage_manager.{h,cpp}: LittleFS mount + read /littlefs/show.shw1 +
  loadShow. format_if_mount_failed for first boot.
- main.cpp F3: setup_show_from_bundle() via applyLoadedShow + DeviceSinkFactory;
  builds PixelMatrix objects from ls.matrices. Falls back to hardcoded patch
  if no bundle. PSRAM-backed bundle buffer.
- samples/{demo.show,dimmer.fdef,head.fdef} + scripts/build_sample_bundle.sh:
  pre-built firmware/main/data/show.shw1 (295 bytes) ships in LittleFS.
- main/CMakeLists: littlefs_create_partition_image packs data/ at flash time.
- glow_core: +apply_loaded_show.cpp. Makefile: +test_apply_loaded_show target.

Host make test: all green (incl. 6 new apply_loaded_show tests).
